            <tr>
                <td class="style5">
                    Interpretation:</td>
                <td class="style6">
                    An increased level indicates 21-hydroxylase deficiency. In patients with 
                    congenital adrenal hyperplasia due to 21-hydroxylase deficiency, monitoring 
                    treatment may require levels at various times of the day.
                    <br />
                    Levels should not be markedly elevated and should not be suppressed immediately 
                    prior to the next dose of glucocorticoid.</td>
            </tr>
